runs.comm: what a ball to start off, this was pushed full which was coming in with the angle, pitches around the off and moves across brushing the pad which evades the keeper too.
this time gets the outside edge, keeper dives but can't reach..length ball and was moving away catching the outside edge..lucky...lucky!
Mustafa comes down the track and Bilal pushes this short and wide across of him, called wide..
met this length ball with a straight bat face, gets it away off the outside edge through backward of point
on a widish length, left alone..
beats the outside edge, on a length and just shade outside off..
came across the line to this length ball and tries to heave it away on the leg side, can't connect once again..
he over-steps, on a length and moving across with the angle, slashes at it and was beaten..
full length ball just outside the off stump, clears the front leg and tries to smack it over the midwicket region. It hits the toe end of the bat, did a bit of damage to his bat..

and he is gone, this is one of the poorest running I have seen this tournament..Length ball around the off stump as Mustafa pushes this by stepping out in front of mid-off and calls for the quick single, Sulehri gets the direct throw at the bowler's end and Mustafa was very casual in his approach, doesn't drag his bat..
on a length and came back in, beaten outside off..
length ball stating on the pads, clips it infront of square leg..
pushes from the crease towards the off side..
clip this length ball down towards the deepish midwicket
length ball, pushes down the ground, not from the meat of the bat, mid-off ran across to cut it off..
touch short on the middle and leg, 134 kph, blocks down the track..
this time down leg, off the glove to on side..
slightly short and moving across with the angle, stays on the crease and belts it nicely over the mid-off region for a boundary
length ball on the middle stump, 133 kph, clips it backward of square leg..
gets an outside edge to this length ball which fall short of first slip..
touch short on the leg, dabs it down to on side..
throws his bat to this length ball, gets an inside edge which went to wide of long leg fence..
length ball comes in with the angle, hits the pad but moving further down..
length ball on the stumps, tucks it away to wide of midwicket
length ball on the middle and leg, clears the front leg and flicks it straight towards the midwicket region, fall short of the diving man there..
short of a length and outside off, cuts it to wide of backward point off the back foot
pushes this back towards the bowler..
back of a length, moves away from outside off, swung hard at it which took the outside edge and flies over the slip cordon ..
once again catches the outside edge to his back of a length ball, went to wide of third man ..
this one drags down the leg side, clips the pad and rolls down the pitch..
back of a length outside off, drags it down to mid-on with a sliding bat..

dropped..length ball on the middle stump, goes for a big hoick down the leg side. It catches the top edge which skies to wide of backward square leg, fielder runs forward and able to get both hands to it but not able to clean it up..keeper too reached there..
length ball angling down the leg side, clips the pad as he misses out the flick..
length ball on middle and leg, clears the front leg and launches this flat over the mid-on region..
full ball angling down leg, clips the pad for a leg bye towards square leg..
met with a straight bat face to work this length ball towards the leg side..
back of a length ball angling down the leg, clips the thigh pad..
slips this length ball down the leg side, called wide..
shortish and slowish outside off, punches it nicely but finds cover..
good length ball straightening on middle, blocks
comes down the track to this short ball outside off, sends it down to long-off for a single
back of a length on the middle stump, stays on the crease and a bottom arm jab to wide of deep midwicket
mistimes this short ball towards the cover
touch uppish this time around off, gets it at the toe end of the bat which went back past the bowler for a couple..
full and wide outside off, stretches his arms and launches this lofted drive over the extra cover..
full and on the middle stump, clips it through midwicket
length ball on the middle stump, quite straightish, stretches out and launches this over the bowler's head..
once again clears the front leg to this short ball, drags it down to long-on
comes down the track, gets to the pitch of it and drives that to wide of long-off for another boundary
tossed up on off, driven to extra cover..
length ball on the middle stump, tucks it to on side..
length ball outside off, pushes through the vacant cover point
once again pushes this length ball, but finds backward of point, not able to direct it
short ball outside off, cross bats it down through midwicket
length ball straightens outside off, runs away to wide of short fine leg off the inside edge..
short and wide outside off, cuts it nicely off the back foot through wide of cover and gets another boundary..
back of a length outside off, works it with an open face and finds short third man..
length ball drifting down the leg side, clears the front leg for a big hoick, beaten..
works this to wide of short fine leg..
slightly short on off, blocks it back towards the bowler
length ball straying on the pads, drills it down to long-on
short of a length and angles back in, mistimes the cut through cover
comes out to this short ball, works it with soft hands to wide of long-on for a couple..
length ball outside off, hoicks that to wide of deep midwicket who ran across to his left and cuts it off
back of a length on middle, skips out and goes through his swinging bat, over the stumps..
back of a length outside off, runs it to wide of diving short third man with an open face
once again short and holds the line outside off, cuts it straight to backward point
length ball straying down the leg, clips it nicely to wide of shortish fine leg and picked a boundary
comes down the track and drops this towards cover with a cross bat hoick..
belts this down the ground towards the sight screen, long-on ran across to his left and slides to save couple of runs..
short and turning in, backs away and swung that nicely by clearing the front leg over the wide of long-on
tucks it through the leg side for a single
flatter length ball on middle, gets a top edge to an attempted sweep, went over short fine leg..
low full toss on the leg, clips it down to deep midwicket
length ball on middle, drills it down to long-on and gets to his fifty

and gets a wicket straight-away, pushes this full ball from wide of the crease as Kaleem clears the front leg and clips it. He does that nicely but not able to pick the gap and also doesn't generate enough power to clear the man at deep midwicket, who juggles but able to hold it..
length ball angling down the leg, clips it it down to deep midwicket
once again flicks this full ball down to deep midwicket
clips it through midwicket and gets back for the second..
fullish ball on the leg, clips it to deep backward square leg..
slowish length ball outside off, pushes to off side..
fullish ball down the leg side, gets down and sweeps it to wide of deep backward square leg
fullish ball outside off, gets down once again to sweep but is beaten as he wears it on the pad, impact outside off
gets an outside edge to a cut which ran away to wide of short fine leg

this time he is gone! Kaleem drags this short as Anwar charges down the track and tries to hoick that away. It was pushed way outside off as he not able to reach for it, ends up with a bottom edge which keeper holds to the perfection..
cuts this short ball through backward of point..

Kaleem yorked Shahzad! Another wicket for him. This was bowled superbly, comes round the wicket and bowls that from wide of the crease, gets the inward angle and was pushed full, right into the block-hole. Shahzad was late to bring his bat down and ball sneaks through and hits the base of the timber..
pokes a length ball outside off, beaten
length ball angling down the leg, clips it behind square leg
beaten outside off..
wait for this short ball and pushes it to the left of the bowler for a quick single..
this one angling down the leg from a length, swivels and helps it away to the long leg fence..
stays in the crease and pushes to cover point..
angling down the leg, clips it around the corner for a single..
beaten outside off as he pushes a length ball outside off..
clips this through the midwicket region for a single
short and outside off, tries to cut but is beaten..
pushes full as he backs away to the leg side  and then tires to reach for it, beaten again..
short of a length and outside off, waits and runs that to wide of third man fence..
drills this full ball down to long-on
fires it full outside off, beaten everyone for a bye..
Usman lofts this down to long-off for a single
full ball which deflects the pad of the keeper and rolls to off side..as batsman can't connect it once again..gets a bye..
comes out and pushes it down to long-off
full and wide ball, driven towards the extra cover
fullish once again from round the wicket, pushes back to the bowler
fuller in length once again, slices it down towards the third man for a single
full ball angling down the leg, backs away and then clears the front leg, launches this to wide of cow corner
slashes this short of a length ball over the wide of deep backward point
full toss angling down the leg, hammers it nicely by staying in the crease over the deep midwicket fielder
clips the boot for a leg bye down towards the leg side for a leg bye..
yorker length outside off, pushes to wide of cover for a single
short ball on the leg, took his eyes off and gets it at the handle of the bat and went to off side
comes out and powers this length ball to wide of long-on and gets a boundary
full and wide outside off, nicely done by Usman, squeezed it through cover point region, fielder ran across but slips through his hands..
nicely drills this down to wide of long-on for a couple..
full ball follows him down the leg as he was backing away, clips it straight down to long-on throat..not able to get the elevation and an easy catch to the fielder down there..
works this nicely over cover point region, short and wide outside off, cuts it nicely and clears the infield..
gets an inside edge to a short ball and went past to wide of short fine leg
this time picks the man down at long-off, skips down the track and tries to hoick it down over the midwicket region. He doesn't get the elevation and a simple catch to Jatinder.
gets an outside edge which deviates the gap at backward point..gets another important boundary..
drills that to wide of long-off for a single
